3 core principles of object oriented programing

	encapsulation
		decoupling, data hiding,
		internal variables are made private, use methods
	polymorphism
		ad hoc-overloading
		dynamic polymorphism-overriding
	inheritance
		extend a class
		override existing methods
		reusing existing code

binary relationship between two classes
	'IS-A' -  relationship
	parent,super class, base class 
		- child, sub class, derived class


